Yes, i managed to reproduce this bug:
The code has compile errors, as i was adding a parameter to the contructor of
the parent exception and all of its subclasses. On the following code, you have
this exception if you refactor the constructor by removing the Object source
parameter. For the first 2 constructors, refactoring works well, but refactoring
the 3rd constructor causes this error. I suppose that the error is caused by the
fact that there are constructors with a similar signature:
ConvertException(Object source, String msgCode, Throwable cause)
ConvertException(Object source, String msgCode, Object param1)

Refactoring on ConvertException(Object source, String msgCode, Throwable cause)
fails.

Hope this helps,
Ludovic

package org.scopemvc.impl.model.convert;

import org.scopemvc.impl.model.ModelException;


/**
 * Exception thrown when an error occured while converting a value with a Converter
 *
 * @author <A HREF="mailto:ludovicc@users.sourceforge.net">Ludovic Claude</A>
 * @version $Revision: 1.10 $ $Date: 2003/11/23 15:28:03 $
 * @created 27 mai 2003
 */
public class ConvertException extends ModelException {
    /**
     * Constructor for ConvertException
     *
     * @param source The source of the exception
     * @param msgCode The code for the error message
     */
    public ConvertException(Object source, String msgCode) {
        super(source, msgCode);
    }

    /**
     * Constructor for ConvertException
     *
     * @param source The source of the exception
     * @param msgCode The code for the error message
     * @param cause The throwable that caused this exception to be thrown
     */
    public ConvertException(Object source, String msgCode, Throwable cause) {
        super(source, msgCode);
        initCause(cause);
    }

    /**
     * Constructor for ConvertException
     * 
     * @param source The source of the exception
     * @param msgCode The code for the error message
     * @param param1 The parameter for the error message
     */
    public ConvertException(Object source, String msgCode, Object param1) {
        super(source, msgCode, param1);
    }

    /**
     * Constructor for ConvertException
     * 
     * @param source The source of the exception
     * @param msgCode The code for the error message
     * @param params The parameters for the error message
     */
    public ConvertException(Object source, String msgCode, Object[] params) {
        super(source, msgCode, params);
    }

}
